name: Buslouis
description:
On the Garvanh peninsula there is a geographical depression from which Lake Bumba emerges. Made up of potassium gas atoms, it can reach temperatures as low as -273 degrees Celsius. 
Inside this lake live the Buslouis, plants that are able to survive such low temperatures. Incredibly, they can live up to 300 years and last a whole year without feeding.
When they swim, they give off certain vibrations from their organism that can be heard outside the lake like songs.
